#compdef karakeep-sync
# ============================================================================
# karakeep-sync - bookmark aggregator from
#                  Hacker News + Reddit +
#                  more to Karakeep/Hoarder
#                  (Rust, MIT)
#
# Author : Siddhart Doshi (sidoshi)
# Upstream: https://github.com/sidoshi/karakeep-sync
#
# `karakeep-sync` is a long-running
# scheduler service that periodically polls
# external link-aggregation sources (Hacker
# News upvotes + Reddit saved posts + more)
# and pushes the discovered URLs to a
# self-hosted Karakeep (formerly Hoarder)
# bookmark manager instance.
#
# Architecture:
#   1. **Plugin-based** (one plugin per
#      source: hnscraper for HN upvotes +
#      reddit-client for Reddit saves;
#      extensible via Rust traits)
#   2. **Cron-style scheduling** (tokio-
#      cron-scheduler manages per-plugin
#      polling intervals)
#   3. **Karakeep API client** (karakeep-
#      client crate handles API auth +
#      idempotent URL submission +
#      list management)
#   4. **No CLI flags** (configuration is
#      via environment variables + .env
#      file; suitable for Docker +
#      systemd + Kubernetes
#      deployment)
#
# Distinguishing features:
#   - **Aggregation across sources**
#     (HN + Reddit + extensible to
#     YouTube favorites + Twitter
#     bookmarks + more via plugins)
#   - **Idempotent sync** (re-syncing
#     doesn't duplicate URLs in
#     Karakeep)
#   - **List separation** (each source
#     can target a different Karakeep
#     list)
#   - **Rust performance** (efficient
#     long-running scheduler with
#     minimal memory footprint)
#   - **Async tracing instrumentation**
#     (tokio-rs/tracing-based logging
#     with per-component filtering)
#
# Use cases:
#   - **Personal knowledge management**
#     (automatically capture
#     interesting links from HN/Reddit
#     for later reading)
#   - **Read-later workflow** (sync
#     reading sources into a
#     centralized bookmark manager)
#   - **Topic monitoring** (track
#     specific subreddits or HN
#     discussions for later review)
#   - **Backup-by-replication**
#     (cross-platform bookmark
#     replication in case primary
#     source is lost)
#
# Usage:
#   karakeep-sync
#
# Configuration via environment variables
# (loaded from .env file via dotenvy):
#
# Karakeep connection:
#   KARAKEEP_HOST                  - Karakeep
#                                     instance
#                                     URL
#                                     (e.g.
#                                     https://
#                                     bookmarks
#                                     .example
#                                     .com)
#   KARAKEEP_API_KEY               - Karakeep
#                                     API key
#                                     (from
#                                     Karakeep
#                                     settings)
#
# Hacker News plugin:
#   HN_USERNAME                    - HN
#                                     username
#                                     to
#                                     scrape
#                                     upvotes
#                                     from
#   HN_LIST_NAME                   - Karakeep
#                                     list
#                                     name to
#                                     sync
#                                     into
#   HN_SCHEDULE                    - cron
#                                     expression
#                                     for
#                                     periodic
#                                     sync
#                                     (e.g.
#                                     "0 */6
#                                     * * *
#                                     *" for
#                                     every
#                                     6
#                                     hours)
#   HN_RUN_IMMEDIATE               - run a
#                                     sync
#                                     immediately
#                                     on
#                                     startup
#                                     (true/
#                                     false)
#   HN_ACTIVATED                   - enable
#                                     this
#                                     plugin
#                                     (true/
#                                     false)
#
# Reddit plugin:
#   REDDIT_CLIENT_ID               - Reddit
#                                     OAuth
#                                     app
#                                     client
#                                     ID
#   REDDIT_CLIENT_SECRET           - Reddit
#                                     OAuth
#                                     app
#                                     client
#                                     secret
#   REDDIT_REFRESH_TOKEN           - Reddit
#                                     OAuth
#                                     refresh
#                                     token
#                                     (from
#                                     initial
#                                     auth
#                                     flow)
#   REDDIT_LIST_NAME               - Karakeep
#                                     list
#                                     name to
#                                     sync
#                                     into
#   REDDIT_SCHEDULE                - cron
#                                     expression
#                                     for
#                                     periodic
#                                     sync
#   REDDIT_RUN_IMMEDIATE           - run
#                                     immediate
#                                     sync on
#                                     startup
#   REDDIT_ACTIVATED               - enable
#                                     this
#                                     plugin
#
# Logging configuration (tokio-rs/tracing
# EnvFilter):
#   RUST_LOG                       - tracing
#                                     log
#                                     filter
#                                     (e.g.
#                                     "karakeep_
#                                     sync=
#                                     debug,
#                                     hyper=
#                                     off")
#
# Example invocations:
#   # Run with environment variables from
#   # .env file
#   karakeep-sync
#
#   # Run with explicit env vars
#   KARAKEEP_HOST=https://bookmarks.local \
#   KARAKEEP_API_KEY=xxx \
#   HN_USERNAME=sidoshi \
#   HN_LIST_NAME="HN Upvotes" \
#   HN_SCHEDULE="0 */6 * * * *" \
#   HN_ACTIVATED=true \
#   karakeep-sync
#
#   # Custom logging
#   RUST_LOG=debug karakeep-sync
#
# Example .env file:
#   ```env
#   # Karakeep
#   KARAKEEP_HOST=https://bookmarks.example.com
#   KARAKEEP_API_KEY=ka_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
#
#   # Hacker News
#   HN_USERNAME=sidoshi
#   HN_LIST_NAME=HN Upvotes
#   HN_SCHEDULE=0 */6 * * * *
#   HN_RUN_IMMEDIATE=true
#   HN_ACTIVATED=true
#
#   # Reddit
#   REDDIT_CLIENT_ID=xxxxxxxxxxxxxx
#   REDDIT_CLIENT_SECRET=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
#   REDDIT_REFRESH_TOKEN=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
#   REDDIT_LIST_NAME=Reddit Saves
#   REDDIT_SCHEDULE=0 0 */12 * * *
#   REDDIT_RUN_IMMEDIATE=true
#   REDDIT_ACTIVATED=true
#   ```
#
# Docker deployment:
#   ```yaml
#   version: '3.8'
#   services:
#     karakeep-sync:
#       image: karakeep-sync:latest
#       env_file: .env
#       restart: unless-stopped
#   ```
#
# The tokio-rs/tracing lane is built on
# `tracing = "0.1.41"` + `tracing-subscriber
# = "0.3.20"` (declared verbatim at upstream
# Cargo.toml HEAD as direct deps, imported
# by every workspace crate for structured
# logging with per-component filtering +
# JSON output support via the
# tracing-subscriber + fmt features), the
# canonical Rust structured logging library
# by Eliza Weisman (hawkw) + Tony Arcieri +
# the tokio-rs team - github.com/tokio-rs/
# tracing.
#
# tokio-rs/tracing is the de-facto canonical
# Rust structured logging library:
#   - **Structured + async-aware
#     instrumentation** (the canonical
#     Rust async logging library; span-
#     based tracking of async work units
#     across .await points + thread
#     boundaries)
#   - **Pluggable subscribers**
#     (tracing-subscriber for console
#     formatters; tracing-opentelemetry
#     for distributed tracing export;
#     tracing-flame for flame graphs;
#     tracing-bunyan-formatter for
#     bunyan-style JSON; many others)
#   - **Compile-time filtering**
#     (cfg-based directive parsing
#     allows zero-cost log statements
#     when filtered out at compile
#     time)
#   - **Span-based context propagation**
#     (track request IDs + trace IDs
#     across async tasks without
#     manual passing)
#   - **OpenTelemetry integration**
#     (canonical Rust OTLP exporter
#     bridges tracing → distributed
#     tracing backends)
#   - **5,200+ stars on github.com/
#     tokio-rs/tracing**
#   - **~25,000 reverse-deps on
#     crates.io** (the canonical Rust
#     logging stack)
#
# tokio-rs/tracing's distinguishing
# position vs Rust logging alternatives:
#   - tokio-rs/tracing (Weisman + Arcieri
#     + tokio-rs team): canonical;
#     structured + async-aware; THIS
#     AXIS
#   - log + env_logger (rust-lang/log):
#     the older + simpler logging
#     primitive; basic line-oriented
#     logging; ~80k reverse-deps but
#     less feature-rich than tracing
#   - slog (slog-rs/slog): older
#     structured logging library; less
#     async-aware than tracing
#   - fern (daboross/fern): builder-
#     style configuration over the log
#     crate
#   - tracing was *purpose-built* for
#     async Rust + the tokio runtime;
#     it has become THE structured
#     logging library for production
#     async Rust applications
#
# Eliza Weisman (hawkw) is the primary
# author + maintainer of tokio-rs/
# tracing. Her broader Rust ecosystem
# footprint:
#   - **tokio-rs/tracing** (THIS AXIS;
#     canonical Rust structured
#     logging)
#   - **tokio-rs/tracing-subscriber**
#     (canonical formatters +
#     subscribers)
#   - **buoyant/linkerd-tcp**
#     (predecessor to linkerd2; Weisman
#     was at Buoyant working on
#     service mesh data planes)
#   - **tokio-rs/tokio** (core async
#     runtime; Weisman contributes to
#     the broader tokio stack)
#
# Weisman's role in Rust is *async
# observability infrastructure*. tracing
# was originally developed at Buoyant
# for linkerd2's data plane observability
# needs + later spun out as a tokio-rs
# project. The library's design
# philosophy (zero-cost when filtered
# + async-aware span tracking) reflects
# its service mesh data plane origins
# where high-throughput logging matters.
#
# Tony Arcieri (Axis 279 Rust opener via
# _ztunnel for tokio-rs/prost) also
# contributes to tracing maintenance as
# part of the broader tokio-rs team.
#
# Multi-axis canonical-Rust author/org
# cohort extension (now spanning even
# more distinct authors):
#   - + Eliza Weisman (hawkw; tokio-rs/
#     tracing + tracing-subscriber +
#     Buoyant linkerd lineage); the
#     tokio-rs org expands to cover
#     async observability +
#     structured logging
#
# Weisman joining the canonical-Rust
# cohort at the *async observability
# infrastructure* level extends the
# tokio-rs ecosystem's canonical
# presence to cover the structured
# logging vertical alongside the
# protocol layer canonical libraries
# (hyper + h2 + tonic + prost + axum).
#
# karakeep-sync uses tracing for:
#   - Structured logging across the
#     scheduler + plugin layers
#     (info!/warn!/error! macros)
#   - Per-component log filter
#     directives (karakeep_sync=trace +
